{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb0a8887d-2930-11f1-a69d-9cbca84c43f0","identifier":"/us/usc/t37/s422"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"422"},"text":"§ 422.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Cadets and midshipmen","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb0a8887e-2930-11f1-a69d-9cbca84c43f0","identifier":"/us/usc/t37/s422/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A cadet at the United States Military Academy, the United States Air Force Academy, or the Coast Guard Academy, or a midshipman at the United States Naval Academy, is entitled to the allowances provided by law for a midshipman in the Navy, and to travel and transportation allowances prescribed under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t37/s452"},"text":"section 452 of this title","children":[],"tail":" while traveling under orders as a cadet or midshipman."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb0a8887f-2930-11f1-a69d-9cbca84c43f0","identifier":"/us/usc/t37/s422/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Each midshipman of the Navy to whom a Navy ration is not furnished is entitled to the commuted value of the ration in money for each day that he is on active duty, including each day that he is on leave. The Secretary of the Navy may prescribe regulations stating the conditions under which the commuted value shall be allowed and may prescribe regulations establishing the rates at which the ration shall be commuted.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb0a88880-2930-11f1-a69d-9cbca84c43f0","identifier":"/us/usc/t37/s422/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" A cadet or midshipman appointed under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2107"},"text":"section 2107 of title 10","children":[],"tail":" is entitled to the same allowances as are provided for cadets and midshipmen at the United States Military, Naval, and Air Force Academies for—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb0a88881-2930-11f1-a69d-9cbca84c43f0","identifier":"/us/usc/t37/s422/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" initial travel to the educational institution in which matriculated;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb0a88882-2930-11f1-a69d-9cbca84c43f0","identifier":"/us/usc/t37/s422/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" travel while under orders; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb0a88883-2930-11f1-a69d-9cbca84c43f0","identifier":"/us/usc/t37/s422/c/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" travel on discharge.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"However, no allowance for travel on discharge may be paid to a discharged cadet or midshipman who continues his scholastic instruction at the same educational institution.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb0a88884-2930-11f1-a69d-9cbca84c43f0"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/649"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–649","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-09-07"},"text":"Sept. 7, 1962","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/76/479"},"text":"76 Stat. 479","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","att